===Etymology===
{{LL.}} ''mediatorem'' "one who mediates," from ''mediatus'', pp. of ''mediari'' "to intervene, mediate," from {{L.}} ''medius'' "middle".
=== Noun ===
'''mediator'''
#One who [[negotiate]]s between parties seeking [[mutual]] agreement

